The paper proposes a new algorithm for learning convolutional neural networks, which is a common technique used in computer vision tasks (cs.CV). The algorithm draws ideas from isotonic regression for learning neural networks (cs.LG) and landscape analysis of non-convex matrix factorization problems (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the potential for further development in designing provable algorithms for learning neural networks and other complex models, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational complexity (cs.SI).
